President Donald Trump spoke separately with King Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud of Saudi Arabia, Crown Prince Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan of Abu Dhabi, and Emir Tamin bin Hamad Al Thani of Qatar. During the calls, Trump expressed his concerns about the ongoing dispute between Qatar and its Gulf and Arab neighbors. He emphasized the importance of stopping terrorist financing and discrediting extremist ideology. Trump also highlighted that unity in the region is crucial to achieving the goals of the Riyadh Summit, which include defeating terrorism and promoting regional stability. However, Trump's main objective is to cease funding for terrorism.